The Health Department is confirming a second case of coronavirus in South Africa. The 39-year-old had been in direct contact with the first case in KZN. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The second case of COVID-19 has been confirmed in South Africa. WATCH: Doctor of SA's first coronavirus patient speaks According to the Health Department, a 39-year-old woman was in direct contact with the first known case of a man in KwaZulu-Natal. She will be admitted to Charlotte Maxeke Hospital in Gauteng for quarantine and treatment. READ: #CoronavirusInSA: How to stay safe The woman was part of a group of 10 that had travelled to Italy. The first patient and his wife were also part of the group. The Ministry has moved to assure the public that the 10 people who travelled on the same flight to Italy are all being tested. It's currently waiting on those results. A second case of Covid-19 has been confirmed. This time it's a 39-year-old who has been in direct contact with the first case from KwaZulu-Natal. Courtesy #DStv403 People who develop symptoms of respiratory illness including cough, fever and shortness of breath - either during or after travel to countries where the coronavirus is circulating, must seek medical care as soon as possible and they must share information about their travel history with healthcare providers. The General Public Hotline Number is 0800 029 999